5. What countries did you visit? england and france

deanna lynn ivy beach.  what a gal. w h a t   a   g a l.

i met deanna in middle school, and i always thought she was nifty. the last few years though i always admired her for her honesty, and confidence, and outgoing-ness.

deanna was always so nice to me, causing me to often wonder why someone as cool as she was didnt hit me upside the head and call me a loser.  she should have. she's so cool she could not use toilet paper and still be hot.



(sorry deanna. thats nasty. my bad)

anyhoo. i miss deanna, and still havent gotten used to not seeing her. its almost like time has stopped, and nothing is going to go one without her here.  i always looked forward to voting her best dressed or coolest ever, but it looks like its up to the californians at her school to carry on the torch.  i only hope that they can fully realize the goddess that she is.






now im sad. i feel like im writing a eulogy. that makes me feel like a terrible person.

this is kind of out of the blue but.... my family had our Hanukkah diner saturday night, and my mom invited over one of her friends... This friend got on the subject of overhearing two men (obviously gay)planning to get together for coffee... she thought this was totally wrong and absurd... and I was just sitting there like "what the hell!"... now I am not gay by any means(my heart belongs to a manly man who likes to experiment with drugs) but what is so terribly wrong with someone choosing who they like or dont't like?.... i dunno   that was terribly out of the blue but it was bothering me so I thought I might tell you


i guess thats all for now
~hug a jew~

oh SNAP.

today mr. nevin was wearing different pants than he normally does.

it was nothing short of amazing.


i need a hobby (or is it hobbie?) outside of livejournaling.

what up.

just finished that lame english journal entry. i effing hate school so much. at least the page-meister dropped that god-awful vocabulary quiz that beat my ass.

so. if you hadnt noticed (which you may not have), i dyed my hair. it didnt turn out how i wanted it to, but at this point, i dont really care.  its just hair, and i just dont care. vanity will not get the best of me........i hope.

ha so i dropped timtim off at the gym after school, and when i picked him up he said that A) mr. wyandt was there and B) he was lifting next to punk rock TONY! ha. i thought it was funny. and C) mr. burke (lame social studies teacher) was there too. he played horse shoes with my cousin. 


sarah call me. i have a funny story.

so anyhoo. nothing else is really new. im not in the mood to spill my guts, not even to put it in a friends only format. i dont really feel like telling people what it is that i am feeling, so if i seem off to you. for christs sake, dont take it personally. i have some things to figure out, im getting sick, im overtired, and i dont want people bothering me and trying to analyze my feelings. 


there my rant is over. i totally didnt even mean to rant either.

my bad.

so tonight. me and sarah and gina were going to color our hair, but it didnt work, and we are postponing this extravaganza. yes, it IS an extravaganza. (thats a fun word to say)

so instead i picked them up and headed over to the waffle house. it was soooo good. they have kickass chocolate pie there. then when i was in the potty, brad (or i guess ben hayes) called, and they were with daria and lia, so they came over. except for ben. we saw him randomly get in someone's car.

then the 7? of us went over to vince's. danielle and brian wilensky were working, so it was cool to seem them.  vince threw dough at me. i felt special. then since i had to take sarah home we left like 15 minutes later, and when sarah called her mom said she could stay out longer so we went back to my house. and we played truth or stationary dare, since none of us wanted to move. 

i dared stacy to pick her nose and eat it.


she did. hah.

we sat there for like an hour. it was good, we caught up on a lot of stuff, and it was enjoyable. a good night all around i guess. 

and now. i think i will go to bed because i am pooped. i get to sleep in tomorrow and i am taking full advantage of that, yo.

i'll leave you with some wisdom:

Yo momma so fat people jog around her for exercise.
Yo momma so stupid it took her 2 hours to watch 60 minutes
Yo momma so old I told her to act her own age, and the bitch died.
Yo momma so nasty She gotta put ice down her drawers to keep the crabs fresh!

alright. thats just gross. nighty night.

this morning the timtim, the padre and i went to the mall to do some xmas shopping. as much as i love this season, i hate hate hate shopping with my father. plus, none of us had a clue as to what to get my mom.  we went everywhere. 

its very warm outside for a december day, in case you hadnt noticed.

i saw kameroski at walmart. i almost started gagging. i ignored him and thankfully didnt have to speak to him. what a jerk he is.

then we went over to starbuck's. i got this really good caramel apple thing, and ally and kit both got little dessert cakes, that i basically ate most of. ooops. my bad.

the we proceeded on to driving aimlessly around clarks summit, and catching up on some good times.

my feet are freezing and i have to go xmas shopping in the morning so perhaps i will go to bed now.
